<H3> <TI>   Denktas Sees Need To Reassess Cyprus Policy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Denktas Sees Need To Reassess Cyprus Policy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2904182194 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2904182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report] </F>
  [Text] Rauf Denktas, president of the Turkish Republic of 
Northern Cyprus, has said that the Turkish Cypriot Government 
and Assembly must reassess the Cyprus policy together with 
Turkey. 
  Addressing a visiting delegation from the Turkish Cypriot 
Fighters Association, Denktas said that the failure to reach an 
agreement on the confidence-building measures [CBM's] shows that 
as long as it is recognized as the legitimate government of 
Cyprus, the Greek Cypriot Administration will not sign an 
agreement with the Turkish Cypriots. 
  Denktas said that it was wrong for UN special envoy Clark to 
have declared the collapse of the talks on the CBM's while in 
the Turkish Cypriot sector. Denktas recalled that the Turkish 
Cypriots conveyed their proposals on four main issues to the 
Greek Cypriots, but the latter rejected them. Denktas said: 
The announcement about the collapse of the talks should have 
been made in the Greek Cypriot sector. 

</TEXT>

