<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Forces Kill 500 `Terrorists' in 20 Days </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Forces Kill 500 `Terrorists' in 20 Days </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA2904070694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 28 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2904070694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Unal Erkan, state of emergency region governor, has 
announced that 500 terrorists were killed in operations 
conducted by security forces in the region and across the border 
in the past 20 days. 
  In statements issued in the Savur District and Kabala 
subdistrict of Mardin, Erkan reported that 500 weapons, eight 
antiaircraft guns, 10 mortars, 74 rocket launchers, and numerous 
rounds of ammunition were seized during the operations. 
Explaining that the terrorists are attacking defenseless 
citizens, Erkan stated that 70 citizens were killed by 
terrorists in the past month. 
  Erkan stressed that the state is determined to completely 
neutralize the terrorists this year. Pointing out that the 
terrorist organization is in the process of collapsing, the 
regional governor remarked that this is leading to internal 
quarrels and executions. Erkan asked the citizens to be careful 
with regard to terrorist incidents and to assist the state even 
more. 

</TEXT>

