<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cetin Returns From Turkmenistan, Uzbekistan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cetin Returns From Turkmenistan, Uzbekistan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3004155094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1435 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA3004155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, April 30 (AA) -- Foreign Minister Hikmet 
Cetin on Saturday [30 April] said that Turkmen natural gas will 
soon be available in Turkey. 
  Speaking to reporters upon his arrival at Ankara's Esenboga 
Airport after concluding official talks in Turkmenistan and 
Uzbekistan, Cetin said his contacts there have been useful. 
  He said during his meeting with Turkmenistan President 
Saparmurad Niyazov, the importance and necessity for Turkmen 
natural gas transfer to Europe via Turkey was once again 
confirmed, expressing hope that its use in Turkey would start in 
1996. 
  Cetin said Turkey will continue to provide support for these 
countries with whom it shares historical, cultural, religious 
and language ties, adding the necessary political will for 
strengthening bilateral relations and cooperation is present. 
  He said foreign trade volume with Turkmenistan is of 161 
million dollars, while it reached 145 million with Uzbekistan, 
and during his visit agreement was reached for increasing it 
even further, adding there is necessary potential for this. 
  Cetin said the Turkish private sector is working in these 
countries in the fields of infrastructure, construction, 
industry and service, expressing hope that greater investments 
will be made in these countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

