<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Juppe Hopes for Continued Cooperation With Italy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Juppe Hopes for Continued Cooperation With Italy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2904160394 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1500 
GMT 29 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2904160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] Silvio Berlusconi has been entrusted with the 
task of forming a new government in Italy. [passage omitted] 
The French Government hopes that close cooperation will 
continue with the Italian Government. Foreign Minister Alain 
Juppe said that it will be necessary to judge on actual evidence: 
  [Begin Juppe recording] Since the birth of the EC, Italy has 
been one of the most fervent players in the construction of the 
Community. I hope it will still be the same. This government 
has just been formed; we do not know its projects. We must 
judge on actual evidence. What is said during an election 
campaign does not always allow one to pass a precise judgement 
on what a government will do after the elections. I think that 
we should wait and see what will happen in the next few weeks 
and months. I really hope that we shall continue to work 
closely with Italy and that what is the very foundation of the 
construction of Europe -- a community of values and the same 
ideas about democracy and the rule of law -- will continue to 
exist in Europe. This is the foundation of European identity 
and of the construction of the European Union. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

