<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   SPD Says Ruehe To Close Down Army Facilities </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    SPD Says Ruehe To Close Down Army Facilities </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0205171294 Hamburg BILD AM SONNTAG in German 1 May 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> AU0205171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg BILD AM SONNTAG </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the view of Social Democratic Party of Germany 
[SPD] defense expert, Erwin Horn, Defense Minister Volker Ruehe 
(Christian Democratic Union --CDU) will have to close down some 
of the Bundeswehr's facilities. Talking to BILD AM SONNTAG, 
Horn said: "Urged by the government coalition, the defense 
minister seems to be planning to cheat the voters. He says that 
all the garrisons will be maintained, even if the Bundeswehr is 
cut down in forces. But in fact, under the Ruehe concept there 
will be several barracks where there will only be uniformed 
caretakers left, who will maintain the buildings. These 
facilities will, of course, no longer be used for military 
purposes. The full truth will not emerge until after the 
Bundestag elections, when a number of barracks will be closed 
down for cost reasons." 
  Horn demands: "The tasks of the Bundeswehr have to be 
clearly defined now, so that the army can be made smaller and 
more efficient." The SPD politician is offering to cooperate on 
this matter: "I will support the CDU minister in this honest 
and important task, even if his concept includes closing down 
several garrisons. But the voters must be told the truth before 
polling day!" 

</TEXT>

