<F P=100> PORTUGAL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mutual Concerns Discussed With Slovakia's Kukan </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mutual Concerns Discussed With Slovakia's Kukan </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD3004190794 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1500 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD3004190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1500 GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Slovak </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The state of Slovak-Portuguese relations and their 
future were evaluated by Slovak Foreign Minister Eduard Kukan 
and Portuguese Foreign Minister Jose Manuel Durao Barroso at 
their meeting at Lisbon today. They observed that there were no 
problems in mutual relations and noted that there were great 
possibilities in developing economic and trade cooperation. 
  Later, Slovak Foreign Minister Eduard Kukan also met Forass 
d'Avella, the Portuguese parliament deputy speaker, who assured 
him that the passage of Slovakia's association agreement with 
the European Union in the Portuguese parliament would be smooth 
in spite of the heavy parliamentary workload. 

</TEXT>

