<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Denmark </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Hopes Serbs `Learned' From Clash With UN </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Hopes Serbs `Learned' From Clash With UN </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0205150594 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1300 GMT 2 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0205150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Danish Defense Minister Hans Haekkerup hopes that 
the Bosnian Serbs learned a lesson from the clash between Serb 
artillery and Danish tanks on Friday [29 April]. The Serb 
troops have announced that nine of their soldiers were killed 
when the tanks -- belonging to the Nordic UN troops -- shelled 
Serb firing positions near the town of Tuzla. Speaking prior to 
the meeting of defense ministers, which has opened in Korsoer in 
Denmark, Haekkerup said that the UN troops must not be passive 
targets but they have at least the right to fire back. 
  The meeting in Korsoer is discussing the Nordic countries' 
peacekeeping operation in Bosnia. The meeting is also attended 
by the UN commander in Bosnia, Michael Rose. 

</TEXT>

