<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Confident About Signing of Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Confident About Signing of Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0205122494 Hamburg DPA in German 1141 GMT 2 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0205122494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stuttgart -- PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat has expressed 
confidence in Stuttgart today regarding the signing of the 
autonomy agreement for Gaza and Jericho. At an international 
news conference at the Daimler-Benz headquarters, 'Arafat 
stated, referring to the meeting between him and Israeli Prime 
Minister Yitzhaq Rabin in Cairo on Tuesday [3 May], that "there 
are still a few problems to be settled." He hopes that it will 
be possible "to eliminate these obstacles" during the talks. 
  Asked about the planned date of the signing of the agreement 
in Cairo on Wednesday, he pointed out: "Where there is a will, 
there is a way." He added: "It takes two to tango, one also 
depends on others." He declined to mention a date as to when he 
will return to Jerusalem, Jericho, and Gaza. It depends on when 
the Israelis will withdraw from these regions. The final 
departure of the Israelis was to have been completed by 13 
April, 'Arafat stressed. "But you see." 
  'Arafat paid a one-day visit to Stuttgart today at the 
invitation of Daimler boss Edzard Reuter. 

</TEXT>

