<H3> <TI>   Weizsaecker Grants Amnesty to Roessner </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Weizsaecker Grants Amnesty to Roessner </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0205091694 Hamburg DPA in German 0906 GMT 2 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU0205091694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- President Richard von Weizsaecker has 
amnestied terrorist Bernhard Roessner (47), who was sentenced to 
life term of imprisonment. This was announced by the 
President's Office in Bonn on Monday [2 May] upon inquiry. The 
amnesty of Roessner, who was involved in the attack on the 
German Embassy in Stockholm in 1975, will become effective on 16 
May. 
  Roessner has been in prison in Straubing for almost 19 
years. 
In November 1992 Justice Minister Sabine 
Leutheusser-Schnarrenberger ordered a suspension of the sentence 
for 18 months because of Roessner's state of health. Since then 
he has been undergoing urgent therapeutical treatment near 
Kassel. 

</TEXT>

