<H3> <TI>   CSU Opens European Election Campaign </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSU Opens European Election Campaign </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU3004155894 Hamburg DPA in German 1428 GMT 30 Apr 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU3004155894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Wuerzburg (DPA) -- On Saturday [30 April] the 
Christian Social Union [CSU] opened its European election 
campaign in Wuerzburg with a commitment to European integration. 
Speaking to 2,000 followers at a European Festival, CSU 
Chairman and FRG Finance Minister Theo Waigel called for a 
Europe of stability, federalism, and diversity. Germany must be 
willing to accept responsibility in Europe and in the world, 
Waigel said. He called for a fair division of the financial 
burdens within the European Union. The return of money to 
Germany must be improved. 
  Bavaria's Minister-President Edmund Stoiber said that anyone 
who is proclaiming a departure from the Maastricht Treaty puts 
Germany's international credibility at stake. However, it must 
be understood as a warning signal that the people's approval for 
European unification is declining to an alarming extent. 
Therefore, the CSU is calling for a reform of the European 
Union "at the head and limbs" and wants to establish more 
"political transparency." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

