<H3> <TI>   Government on Reopening Border Gate With Iraq </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government on Reopening Border Gate With Iraq </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0205160094 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1500 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0205160094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Diyarbakir, May 2 (A.A.) -- Deputy Prime Minister 
Murat Karayalcin said on Monday [2 May] that the government 
would evaluate reopening the Habur border gate which borders 
Turkey and Iraq. 
  Karayalcin speaking to reporters at his arrival in 
southeastern Diyarbakir Province for studies on the Habur border 
gate which is near the township of Silopi in the province of 
Sirnak said reopening this border gate was very important for 
trade in the southeast. 

</TEXT>

