<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Council Reviews Antiterrorism Struggle </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Council Reviews Antiterrorism Struggle </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA3004181294 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 30 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA3004181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Statement" issued by the National Security Council] </F>
  [Text] In its meeting today, the National Security Council 
[NSC] reviewed the security and law and order situation 
throughout the country as well as the internal and external 
developments that affect this situation. 
  The NSC appraised the results of the struggle waged against 
the domestic and foreign activities of the separatist terrorist 
organization and its supporters aimed at disrupting the 
indivisible unity of our state and the tranquillity and security 
of our people. The NSC was pleased to observe the successful 
results of this struggle. The Council stressed the need to 
utilize all means available to the state and continue the 
support accorded to the struggle waged by our security forces in 
a bid to totally neutralize such separatist activities and 
establish security and tranquillity in all parts of the country. 
  Furthermore, the NSC underlined that, in accordance with the 
importance Turkey attaches to peace, stability, and security in 
the regional and international spheres, diplomatic efforts for 
the solution of existing problems should continue with 
determination. 

</TEXT>

