<H3> <TI>   Ciller Comments on Iraqi Pipeline, U.S. Note </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ciller Comments on Iraqi Pipeline, U.S. Note </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0305124694 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1200 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0305124694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] Addressing a True Path Party 
[TPP] meeting today, Prime Minister Tansu Ciller, leader of the 
TPP, pointed out that the Turkish economy is being negatively 
affected by the economic embargo against Iraq. 
  [Begin Ciller recording] The oil pipeline system, which 
constitutes a valuable investment for both Turkey and Iraq, has 
been left idle for three years and faces the danger of damage 
and rotting. An agreement has been reached to carry out a sort 
of rescue operation in order to eliminate this danger. In this 
way, when the oil embargo is lifted in the future, the system 
will be able to function uninterruptedly. [end recording] 
  Ciller explained that oil will be pumped to the pipeline and 
that food, medicine, and certain basic necessities will be sent 
to Iraq in return. The prime minister denied reports that the 
United States gave Turkey a note in connection with this matter. 
She stressed that the allies realize that this situation arose 
because of a technical necessity. 

</TEXT>

