<H3> <TI>   European Court: Belgium Guilty of Discrimination </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    European Court: Belgium Guilty of Discrimination </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0305144594 Paris AFP in English 1352 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0305144594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Luxembourg, May 3 (AFP) -- The European Court of 
Justice ruled Tuesday [3 May] that Belgium was guilty of 
discrimination against foreign students from other European 
Union [EU] countries. 
  It said in a ruling that Belgium had flouted EU treaties by 
asking students from other EU countries to pay higher enrollment 
fees than non-Belgians. 
  The Court also blasted Belgium for fixing a 2-percent quota 
on the number of EU students which Belgian universities must 
mandatorily enroll. 
  The ruling followed a plea lodged by the European 
Commission, 
whose job it is to check that member states stick by EU rules. 

</TEXT>

