<F P=100> BENELUX COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Netherlands </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Flying Brigades' To Combat Illegal Immigration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Flying Brigades' To Combat Illegal Immigration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0305135294 Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD in Dutch 2 May 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> BR0305135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rotterdam NRC HANDELSBLAD </F>
<F P=105>  Dutch </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Flying Brigades Begin Controls"] </F>
  [Text] Around 200 military police began carrying out 
controls this morning on foreigners who cross the border from 
Germany and Belgium. Checks are also being carried out on 
international trains. This monitoring is the result of 
agreements reached between the government and Second Chamber in 
order to halt the increase in the number of illegal foreigners 
entering the Netherlands. It principally concerns people who 
enter the Netherlands illegally or asylum-seekers who have no 
chance of receiving a residence permit. The so-called flying 
brigades will be in action 24 hours a day. 

</TEXT>

