<F P=102>   LD0305155494 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 1445 GMT 
3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305155494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The consultations over the make-up of the cabinet 
will end on 6 May. On 7-8 May, "the situation will be examined 
by the members of the Freedom Alliance," and on 8 May, Prime 
Minister Silvio Berlusconi will break his silence. 
  Berlusconi is being cautious over the timetable and is 
denying that there are obstacles concerning the possible make-up 
of the government: "I believe that there will not be any 
opposition." The government's program is "very advanced" and 
will only be revealed when it will be presented to the Chamber 
of Deputies. He also confirmed that there would be a meeting 
this evening at 2100 hours between the heads of the parties in 
the Freedom Alliance. Umberto Bossi will also be present at the 
meeting. 

</TEXT>

