<H3> <TI>   FRG's Kohl Meets With Vatican Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    FRG's Kohl Meets With Vatican Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305212794 Rome RAI Uno Television Network in Italian 1800 
GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0305212794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Uno Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chancellor Helmut Kohl is visiting Italy. He was to 
have been received in the Vatican by Pope John Paul II, but 
because of the Pope's accident, he was received by the Vatican's 
head of state, Cardinal Angelo Sodano. Kohl gave an interview 
to Paolo Borrella. 
  [Begin recording] [Borrella] Is the destiny of Germany still 
that of a united Europe, as you said at the time of 
reunification? 
  [Kohl, in German with superimposed Italian translation] 
Adenauer said in 1950 that the reunification of Germany and the 
unification of Europe were two sides of the same coin. If the 
German people who received this gift of reunification now 
concentrate only on themselves, then they would not be worthy of 
this historic duty. We need European unity just as much as the 
air that we breathe. In the 21st century there will be neither 
peace nor liberty for the European people unless we pursue and 
realize this ideal. However, we are already on the right road. 
We are not forgetting the others. There are millions of human 
beings in the Balkans who are waiting for our help, and there 
are billions of people in the third world who are also waiting 
for our help. It is a duty that we must not shirk. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

