<F P=100> GREECE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Meets With Albania's Serreqi </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Meets With Albania's Serreqi </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0305123594 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1130 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0305123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shortly before leaving for Zurich from Ioannina, 
Foreign Minister Karolos Papoulias expressed reserved optimism 
on the outcome of his meeting with his Albanian counterpart, 
Alfred Serreqi. He stressed: I am going to this meeting with 
open proposals and I hope that Albania will show it willingness 
to improve bilateral relations. 
  The Greek foreign minister said he will raise the issue of 
Albania releasing the arrested members of the Greek minority 
party Omonoia, who are being detained at Tirana prison. 
Papoulias added that the recent incidents in Tirana have cast a 
shadow on this meeting in Zurich, and as a gesture of goodwill 
the Albanian Government should have already released the 
prisoners. 
  Referring to the recent incident at the Episkopi border 
station, Papoulias reiterated that it would not be beneficial 
for the Albanian side to insist on its intransigent position. 
  The ATHENS NEWS AGENCY reported a short time ago that the 
meeting between Papoulias and Serreqi began at 1300 today [Greek 
time] in Zurich. The bulletin adds that Foreign Ministry 
Secretary General Ambassador Khristos Zakharakis and other 
officials participated in the meeting, which will deal with the 
entire spectrum of Greek-Albanian relations, particularly the 
issue of the oppressive measures adopted recently against the 
Greek minority. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

