<H3> <TI>   Spokesman, Pangalos Clarify Position on FYROM </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman, Pangalos Clarify Position on FYROM </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0305170694 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1500 GMT 3 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0305170694 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government Spokesman Evangelos Venizelos has 
stressed that the Greek positions on the issue of Skopje [The 
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM] are known and 
established. The spokesman made the above statement on the 
occasion of Alternate Foreign Minister Theodhoros Pangalos's 
interview with LA REPUBBLICA. 
  During that interview, Pangalos referred to the mutual 
right, 
or mutual demand as he later corrected it, by Greece and Skopje 
for the term "Macedonia." In the same interview, Pangalos said 
that Greece will lift the embargo against Skopje if Skopje 
removes the Sun of Veryina [from its symbols] and makes a 
clarifying declaration regarding the disputed articles of its 
constitution. 
  In an interview on FLASH Radio [Athens-based private radio 
station] this morning, Pangalos said that he was referring to a 
mutual demand and not to a mutual right to the term "Macedonia." 
  On this issue, the government spokesman said: I think that 
to search for very specific expressions or interpretations of 
expressions, does not help the execution of our foreign affairs. 

</TEXT>

