<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bonn Lifts Ban on Arms Deliveries to Turkey </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bonn Lifts Ban on Arms Deliveries to Turkey </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0405110194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0946 GMT 4 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0405110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- The German Government has lifted 
its ban on arms deliveries to Turkey. This was announced in 
Bonn today by Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel. 
  Kinkel pointed out that the Federal Defense Ministry has 
evaluated the photographs given to the Foreign Ministry "as 
proof of Turkey's use of weapons and equipment from military aid 
programs contrary to the terms of the agreement." The result is 
that "use contrary to the terms of the agreement cannot be 
proved on the basis of the photographs." The German Government 
has therefore decided to resume the deliveries to Turkey as 
stipulated in the agreements on NATO defense aid, material aid, 
and special arms aid. 

</TEXT>

