<H3> <TI>   Energy Minister Leaves for Talks in Egypt </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Energy Minister Leaves for Talks in Egypt </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0405101194 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1450 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0405101194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Istanbul, May 3 (A.A.) -- Energy Minister Veysel 
Atasoy left for Egypt on Tuesday [3 May] as the official guest 
of Egyptian Electric and Energy Minister Mahir Abazah. 
  He told reporters at Istanbul's Ataturk Airport that during 
his visit talks will be held on the possibilities of increasing 
present cooperation in the field of energy. 
  Atasoy said discussions will also take place on the setting 
up of an inter-connection system (United Energy Distribution 
System) between Turkey, Egypt, Jordan, Syria, and Iraq. 

</TEXT>

