<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Assembly Speaker Cindoruk Leaves for France </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA0205111394 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1005 GMT 2 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA0205111394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Istanbul, May 2 (A.A.) -- Parliament Speaker 
Husamettin Cindoruk on Monday [2 May] said that relations with 
France are at a perfect level in all fields and this also 
reflects interparliamentary relations. 
  He was speaking to reporters at Istanbul's Ataturk Airport 
before his departure for France where he will be the official 
guest of his French counterpart Philippe Seguin. 
  During his stay Cindoruk is also scheduled to meet French 
President Francois Mitterrand, Deputy Parliament Speaker Eric 
Raoult [name as received] and a reporter from LE FIGARO 
newspaper on May 2. 
  He will also meet several other senior French officials on 
May 3- 4, and attend a ceremony which will be organized at the 
French Parliament. 
  Cindoruk said the visit will favorably contribute to 
bilateral relations. 
  He is expected back in Turkey on May 4. 

</TEXT>

