<H3> <TI>   Meets With President Demirel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets With President Demirel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0305215394 Tehran IRNA in English 2056 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0305215394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, May 3, IRNA -- Iranian Deputy Foreign 
Minister Mohammad Hashemi here Tuesday night [3 May] in his 
visit with Turkish President Suleyman Demirel called for 
expansion of Tehran-Ankara cultural and security cooperation. 
  Hashemi said that his first official visit to Turkey was 
made 
because he highly valued promotion of cooperation between the 
two neighbouring countries. 
  "During my short stay in Turkey, useful discussions were 
made 
with the Turkish officials in the field of mutual, regional as 
well as international development which concluded with positive 
outcome," Hashemi said. 
  He termed Iran-Turkey eco-political ties as "satisfactory" 
and called for further expansion of ties in the field of culture 
and security. 
  Hashemi arrived in Ankara yesterday and has so far met with 
Turkish Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin and Interior Minister 
Nahit Mentese. 

