<H3> <TI>   PKK Opens `Information' Office in Madrid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PKK Opens `Information' Office in Madrid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0405082294 Istanbul HURRIYET in Turkish 30 Apr 94 p 16 </F>
<F P=103> NC0405082294 </F>
<F P=104>  Istanbul HURRIYET </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Zeynel Lule: "A PKK Office in Spain"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Strasbourg--The Workers Party of Kurdistan [PKK] 
has opened an office in Madrid under the guise of a Kurdish 
Information Center. The opening ceremony on 27 April was 
attended by many members of parliament and several 
representatives of ERNK [Kurdish People's Liberation Front], 
which is the PKK's armed wing. 
  The daily EL PAIS has reported that Faruk Dogru, a 
representative of ERNK, addressed the ceremony and urged the 
Spanish Government to direct pressure on Turkey. He also said 
that Spain's support would be sought in the struggle through the 
center in Madrid and initiatives launched with the Spanish 
Government for a military embargo against Turkey. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

