<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   International Press Institute Sets Up Russian Committee </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    International Press Institute Sets Up Russian Committee </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0305173594 Paris AFP in English 1606 GMT 3 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0305173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vienna, May 3 (AFP) -- The International Press 
Institute [IPI], made up of journalists from 85 countries 
fighting for freedom of the press, Tuesday [3 May] set up an IPI 
Russian Committee, a statement from the organisation said. 
  The IPI said Russian media faced serious economic and 
administrative problems as well as a poor distribution system. 
  The new IPI cell in Russia will report back to the central 
secretariat on the free flow of information and on general 
developments in the media. 

</TEXT>

