<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mock Reacts to Vote </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mock Reacts to Vote </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU0405173894 Vienna Oesterreich Eins Radio Network in German 
1600 GMT 4 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0405173894 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna Oesterreich Eins Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Foreign Minister Alois Mock in Vienna on 4 May </F>
-- recorded] 
  [Text] I would like to announce that the European 
Parliament has voted in favor of agreeing to Austrian membership 
in the European Union [EU] with a majority of 374 votes, 24 no 
votes, and 61 abstentions. I would like to point out that, for 
me, this signifies an appreciation of the remarkable course our 
country has taken since 1945. I also think this recognizes our 
political and social stability as well as the achievements of 
our country. I think this vote also appreciates Austria's role 
and implies an obligation for Austria regarding its historical 
relations with the countries of Central and East Europe. Last 
but not least, it also shows that Austria is a valuable and 
natural partner for the EU. With today's vote, the nations of 
Europe that are members of the EU have invited the Austrian 
people to contribute their share as partners in a peaceful 
future. I am convinced that the Austrian people will give a 
positive answer on 12 June. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
